---
description: BRAIN Framework routing rule
globs:
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/fm/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/fm/**/*.md"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/pm/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/pm/**/*.md"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/kc/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/kc/**/*.md"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/sm/**/*.mdx"
  - "docs/biological-targets/**/sm/**/*.md"
alwaysApply: true
---

Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

This rule determines which schema applies to each page type.

Routing logic:

- If the file path contains `/fm/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/functional-mechanism-schema.md`

- If the file path contains `/pm/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md`

- If the file path contains `/kc/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/key-constraint-schema.md`

- If the file path contains `/sm/`:
  - Apply:
    `system/specific-mechanism-schema.md`

Section body prose (all PM / FM / SM / KC pages):
- Follow `system/mechanism-page-section-prose.md` — sections must not restate title, entity ID, BRS name/number, or Definition; each section follows only its schema role.

Conflict prevention:

- Must not mix FM, PM, KC, and SM schemas in the same file
- Must not infer page type from content; use file path only

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
